1. lspci – List PCI Devices
Shows devices connected to the PCI bus (like internal hardware)

Example output:

00:1f.2 SATA controller: Intel Corporation ...
01:00.0 VGA compatible controller: NVIDIA ...

Devices shown: graphics cards, network cards, sound cards, SATA controllers, etc.

$ lspci

2. lsblk – List Block Devices

Shows storage devices (block-level): hard drives, SSDs, USB drives, etc.

Example output:

NAME   MAJ:MIN RM SIZE RO TYPE MOUNTPOINT
sda      8:0    0 500G  0 disk 
└─sda1   8:1    0 500G  0 part /

Use this to check what drives are connected and mounted.

Use it like:

$ lsblk

3. lsusb – List USB Devices

Shows all devices connected to USB ports

Example output:

Bus 001 Device 002: ID 046d:c534 Logitech USB Receiver
Bus 002 Device 003: ID 0781:5567 SanDisk USB Flash Drive

Use it like:

$ lsusb

